1
00:00:00,100 --> 00:00:05,589
My non-CS branch engineers, this one's especially for you.

2
00:00:05,539 --> 00:00:09,460
Background doesn't matter, preparation does.

3
00:00:09,460 --> 00:00:12,776
I know you're tempted to skip ahead.

4
00:00:12,776 --> 00:00:14,157
Don't.

5
00:00:14,157 --> 00:00:18,407
This is the part that gets asked in interviews.

6
00:00:18,407 --> 00:00:28,513
A topic is a named, durable, ordered log of records — conceptually similar to a database table, but append-only and replayable.

7
00:00:28,513 --> 00:00:33,276
Every topic is divided into one or more partitions.

8
00:00:33,276 --> 00:00:39,315
A partition is the fundamental unit of parallelism and ordering in Kafka.

9
00:00:39,315 --> 00:00:45,973
Real talk: I've seen senior engineers at Uber get this wrong in interviews.

10
00:00:45,973 --> 00:00:48,368
Don't be that person.

11
00:00:48,368 --> 00:00:52,460
Everyone says Replication is the best approach.

12
00:00:52,460 --> 00:00:57,065
That is , actually wrong for most real-world systems.

13
00:00:57,065 --> 00:01:00,092
I will show you why in a moment.

